<title type="html"><![CDATA[Loading CHR Data with Emulation]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1030&amp;p=8783#p8783"><![CDATA[
The first 8k (hex $2000) of PPU memory is where the pattern tables are stored. This is where the CHR ROM is loaded into. The iNES header has two bytes in it one for PRG ROM and the other for CHR ROM. Byte 6 is the number of CHR ROM pages within the ROM. These are loaded at the same time the PRG ROM are.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=191">WedNESday</a> — Sun Jan 29, 2006 1:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
